Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%labels
Author integration-prep
Description Container image for SSH-key generation task. Provides a clean
           environment where no key material exists yet and pytest is
           available for automated grading.

%post
    set -eux

    # Update package lists and install required software.
    apt-get update
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3 \
        python3-pip \
        openssh-client \
        ca-certificates \
        locales

    # Generate a minimal UTF-8 locale to keep Python happy.
    locale-gen en_US.UTF-8

    # Install pytest for the grader/agent.
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Create an unprivileged user called "user" with home /home/user.
    # Do NOT create ~/.ssh; the grading rubric requires it to be absent or
    # to have strict permissions if it does exist.  We leave it absent.
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    useradd --create-home --shell /bin/bash user

    # Ensure sane permissions on the new home directory.
    chmod 755 /home/user
    chown -R user:user /home/user

    # Clean up apt caches to keep the image small.
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

%environment
    export LC_ALL=en_US.UTF-8
    export LANG=en_US.UTF-8
    export PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin

%runscript
    # Default runscript: drop into a shell as root for ad-hoc debugging.
    exec /bin/bash "$@"

%help
This image is prepared for an exercise where the learner must create an
Ed25519 key-pair, register it for password-less SSH, and log metadata.
The container intentionally starts without any ~/.ssh material so that
the learner can generate it from scratch. Pytest is pre-installed for
automated test execution.